-- Russia’s Slavneft Sells 51.9% Stake in Mendeleev Oil Refinery
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-05-22T08:18:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/russia-s-slavneft-sells-51-9-stake-in-mendeleev-oil-refinery.html
OAO Slavneft, jointly owned by OAO
Gazprom Neft and  BP Plc (BP/) ’s Russian venture, sold a 51.9 percent
stake in the Yaroslavl-based Mendeleev refinery to ZAO
Neftgazsbyt, the company said today in a  statement .  Slavneft’s board of directors decided in 2007 to sell the
refinery, which can process of 500,000 metric tons of crude a
year, or 10,000 barrels a day, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
